Thanks @doncat! So if I understand correctly, the "metadata: none" option just means the container information will not be merged into a Voyager or ASpace record, right? So it's a "labels only" workflow?

If so, in addition to the above, we need to allow for the following:

* allow barcode to be blank
* persist ALL AbID's for future reference

workflows to accommodate: 
*ASpace, as above
*Voyager: output XML file to be picked up by DT's macro for further processing
*none:  output XML file to be picked up by DT's macro for further processing

NB: Tentatively, we think the ASpace workflow doesn't need to output labels (ASpace includes a labels functionality--it's currently returning a 404, but we're following up with Lyrasis). The Voyager / no metadata workflows do, but that can hopefully be picked up by the existing tool for now (until we change over to Alma).

pulfalight.title: Improve the error handling for ASpaceIndexJob#perform

comments.body:
As logged within Honeybadger, there are cases in which HTTP request errors are encountered when attempting to synchronize the ArchivesSpace EAD XML into PULFALight. Please see the following backtrace:

```ruby
aspace_index_job.rb  46 perform(...)
[PROJECT_ROOT]/app/jobs/aspace_index_job.rb:46:in `perform'
44 
45   def perform(resource_descriptions_uri:, repository_id: nil)
46     ead_content = aspace_client.get("#{resource_descriptions_uri}.xml", query: { include_daos: true, include_unpublished: false }, timeout: 1200).body.force_encoding("UTF-8")
47     xml_documents = Nokogiri::XML.parse(ead_content)
48     xml_documents.remove_namespaces!
```

I would propose that this also be scoped to handle authentication errors, such as `ArchivesSpace::ConnectionError: Failed to connect to ArchivesSpace backend as [USER]` (please see https://app.honeybadger.io/projects/65922/faults/70808284 for an example of this).
We do need these jobs to error so they'll retry. We could ignore the errors in Honeybadger?
